                            <comment id="15379960" author="jking3" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 19:24:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for opening a Jira item to track, and for re-enabling some make cross tests that were known to fail.  We should really clean all of those up... each one likely represents a bug like this one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15379990" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 19:42:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user Jens-G commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Good catch!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    What about other languages? Did you check all of them? &lt;br/&gt;
    =&amp;gt; If yes, what was the result? &lt;br/&gt;
    =&amp;gt; If not, why not? &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Could you do that?&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="15380051" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 20:27:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user binaryseed commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Unfortunately, adding back in the cross language tests still causes failures &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Seems like there are other bugs lurking beyond the boolean one here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ```&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
