		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;Following 9 failures were unexpected ***:&lt;br/&gt;
    csharp-erl              compact      buffered-ip-ssl          failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    csharp-erl              compact      framed-ip-ssl            failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-nodejs              compact      buffered-ip              failure(timeout)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-cpp                 compact      buffered-ip              failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-cpp                 compact      buffered-ip-ssl          failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-cpp                 compact      framed-ip                failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-cpp                 compact      framed-ip-ssl            failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-rb                  compact      buffered-ip              failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    erl-rb                  compact      framed-ip                failure(1)&lt;br/&gt;
    ```&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="15380054" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2016 20:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user binaryseed commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I didn&apos;t check out all the languages, just a handful to verify that the spec is: true = 1, false = 2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382196" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 12:24:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user nsuke commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    @binaryseed thanks, I&apos;ve verified your patch locally and it does fix the problem. It&apos;ll be merged soon.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I&apos;m also working on extending cross tests so that we can assert true/false and endianess which cannot be verified by current round trip tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382347" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 14:23:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user asfgit closed the pull request at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382358" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 14:29:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user jeking3 commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Aren&apos;t we supposed to have a clean build before merging?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382376" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 14:40:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user nsuke commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    The failures are from tentative re-activation submitted later as a separate commit&lt;br/&gt;
    I&apos;ve excluded it from the merge.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382384" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 14:48:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user jeking3 commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Would I be able to tell that happened from any log or history that is public?  From here it looks like the tests were re-enabled because you merged the hash with them enabled (d150f8b).  I think it is important to have a clean and visible history so everyone knows what&apos;s going on.  If in effect you simply merged 49cefb9 by reverting the changes in d150f8b before pushing, that makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15382395" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 18 Jul 2016 14:55:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user nsuke commented on the issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/1049&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    In my environment d150f8b41ef3a3f63fadcc595a99bc38628cd636 looks exactly same as 49cefb9563a18bc1cc7ac70ad0f1830019a3cd65 ...&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
